default4. defaultConclusion: defaultACEVO’s principles for good paydefault&#xa0;default4.1 
defaultAbove all, ACEVO believes that good pay for any charity employee means charity beneficiaries, donors and employees agree that it provides good value for money.default4.2 Recent opinion polls show 
defaultcharities are among the most trusted organisations in society
default, but that the public are also concerned about the pay of charity leaders.
default ACEVO acknowledges concer
defaultns expressed by members of the Public Administration Select Committee 
defaultand the wider public th
defaultat methods of setting pay in the sector may not be sufficiently transparent, and works constantly to promote transparency and an emphasis on 
defaultvalue for money within the sector
default. The ACEVO Pay Survey has been 
defaultpublishing data
default on the pay practices of the sector
default every year 
defaultfor more than
default 
defaulttwo decades
default, 
defaulta
defaultnd is established as the market-leading benchmark of pay for the sector’s largest charities.  We hope 
defaultto continue working to
default establish best practice 
defaulton 
defaultthe setting of 
defaultChief Executive pay 
defaultacross the sector
default,
default and ensure
default that charities remain among our country’s most trusted organisations.
